The paper deals with cross-modal similarity search, which involves computer vision (CV) and information retrieval (IR) tasks. The proposed approach involves deep learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (LG). The paper also mentions experiments on two popular benchmarks, which suggests that it could fall under multimedia (MM) or computational linguistics (CL) categories as well.
